  "prompt": "When will Intel start hiring new candidates following the 2016 layoffs?",
  "response": "Intel, like many large corporations, continuously assesses its hiring needs based on business demands, project timelines, and strategic goals. Following the layoffs in 2016, Intel did not publicly announce a specific date for when they would start hiring new candidates. However, companies often begin hiring again once they have restructured and identified new areas of growth or need.\n\nIf you're interested in opportunities at Intel, I recommend:\n\n1. **Regularly Checking Their Careers Page:** Intel's official careers website would list new openings as they become available.\n2. **Networking:** Connect with current Intel employees through LinkedIn or industry events to gain insights into potential hiring trends.\n3. **Following Intel News:** Keep an eye on press releases and news articles about Intel's strategic direction, which might hint at upcoming hiring needs.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, contacting Intel's HR department directly would be the best course of action.",
